- The integer array parameter `orders` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `orders` must have a length between 1 and 100000.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `orders` must be an array of length 3.
- The integer elements `price`, `amount`, and `orderType` in each element of the integer array parameter `orders` must be between 1 and 1000000000.
- The integer result is the total amount of orders in the backlog after processing all orders from the input.
- The integer result is calculated modulo 1000000007.